OL,3,CMother-of-two operated on by disgraced
OL,4,Csurgeon not given 'safest' treatment
OL,6,FGiving evidence to the judge-led
OL,7,Finquest, Mr Baker said he and his
OL,8,Fwife, who was also an assistant
OL,9,Fheadteacher, had borrowed #12,000 to
OL,10,Fpay for the 2005 operation to be
OL,11,Fcarried out privately.
OL,13,FMr Baker told the court Mrs Baker, who
OL,14,Fwas diagnosed with invasive cancer in
OL,15,Fher right breast in February 2005, was
OL,16,Fadamant that she wanted a mastectomy
OL,17,Fwithout reconstruction as "she didn't
OL,18,Fwant to take any risks".
OL,26,@yD@[OUzD@WO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/14
