OL,3,CMother-of-two operated on by disgraced
OL,4,Csurgeon not given 'safest' treatment
OL,6,FHis wife was diagnosed with cancer for
OL,7,Fa second time in July 2007 and was
OL,8,Fagain seen by Paterson, who again
OL,9,Fsuggested reconstructive surgery,
OL,10,Fwhile she "wanted to do whatever was
OL,11,Fthe safest".
OL,13,FMr Baker said of Paterson: "He just
OL,14,Fsaid unfortunately this sometimes
OL,15,Fhappens. Chris was very concerned with
OL,16,Fit being a recurrence and she wanted
OL,17,Fit removed as quickly as she could."
OL,26,@rD@KOUsD@KO]uD@\OUyD@dO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/14
