OL,3,CMother-of-two operated on by disgraced
OL,4,Csurgeon not given 'safest' treatment
OL,6,FMr Jones asked Mr Baker: "Were you
OL,7,Faware of that higher risk?"
OL,9,FMr Baker answered: "No. It was never
OL,10,Ffully explained to us what the
OL,11,Fdifference of opinion was."
OL,13,FIn his statement paying tribute to his
OL,14,Fwife, which was read to the court on
OL,15,Fhis behalf by the coroner, Mr Baker
OL,16,Fsaid: "When she had to take early
OL,17,Fretirement through ill health, she
OL,18,Freceived so many letters and cards
OL,19,Ffrom pupils, ex-pupils and staff,
OL,20,Fthanking her for all the help, support
OL,21,Fand encouragement she had given them.
OL,26,@nD@ZOUoD@[O]qD@TOUsD@[O]xD@GOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G11/14
